1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on a reconfigurable robot model and provides an algorithm for planning and executing robot motion. This makes cs.RO the most likely sub-category.
2. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper discusses a model of robots that can slide across each other and rotate about each others' edges, which could be considered a multi-agent system. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the control of a reconfigurable robot system, which falls under the scope of cs.SY.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The algorithm for planning and executing robot motion could be considered an AI technique.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper provides an algorithm for planning and executing robot motion, which falls under the scope of cs.DS.
